'''Battle Cross''' is a [[shoot 'em up]] released in arcades by Omori Electric (also known as Omori Electronic) in 1982.<ref name=klov>{{KLOV game|id=7039|name=Battle Cross}}</ref> The player controls a fighter [[spacecraft]] by moving around the screen and shooting enemies. In 1984 [[Sony]] published a version for the Sony Hit-Bit 75 [[MSX]] computer.<ref name=hitbit>{{cite web |title=Battle Cross Hit-Bit MSX Manual |url=https://archive.org/details/BattleCross |website=archive.org |publisher=Sony |date=1984}}</ref>

